    <text>
        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>DR. J. SOLIS&#45;COHEN&#44;<lb/>
                OFFICE HOURS&#58; 9&#45;1.<lb/></p>
            <p>1431 Walnut Street&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia&#44; Sept 6 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear teacher&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>I had wished to<lb/> call on you &#38; submit<lb/> to your judgment&#44; a project<lb/> I am very anxious should<lb/> be instituted after the holy&#45;<lb/>days&#59; and to get you to prepare<lb/> the preliminary papers.<lb/></p>
            <p>It is this.  A revision<lb/> of the <del>ritual</del> liturgy has become<lb/> absolutely needful in order to preserve<lb/> and conserve&#45;&#45;Conservative<lb/> congregations&#45;&#45;especially<lb/> yours &#38; H. P. Mendes&#44; or which<lb/> now&#44; all depends.  Unless<lb/> you take the lead&#44; the con&#45;<lb/>gregations will do it&#44; with<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>disastrous results&#45;&#45;especially<lb/> in New York.  Here&#44; perhaps<lb/> we can prevent it by judic&#45;<lb/>ious management&#45;&#45;leave<lb/> it to me&#44; at all events&#44; and<lb/> I will advise you from<lb/> time to time of anything<lb/> of importance.  I had a<lb/> conversation with Dropsie<lb/> the other day&#44; in which I<lb/> made him virtually retract<lb/> what he had said before&#45;&#45;<lb/> at least to explain that<lb/> he did not mean our Chazan<lb/> but that some other Chazan<lb/> might &#38;c. &#38;c.&#45;&#45;which is<lb/> one step gained by humoring<lb/> instead of fighting him<lb/></p>
            <p>However there is a constant<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>2<lb/></p>
            <p>pressure in both synagogues<lb/> that I fear cannot long<lb/> be held in check&#45;&#45;we<lb/> must be prepared to<lb/> yield somewhat or be<lb/> broken&#45;&#45;and the danger<lb/> to the cause of a break&#44;<lb/> you can appreciate.<lb/></p>
            <p>I therefore suggest that<lb/> the Seminary invite congre&#45;<lb/>gations in sympathy to form<lb/> a synod of one clerical &#38;<lb/> one lay delegate each to<lb/> form an American liturgy.<lb/></p>
            <p>To have optional and<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>fixed liturgies&#45;&#45;<lb/>  The fixed to contain<lb/> what embodies principles&#44;<lb/> the optional to be left<lb/> to each congregation.<lb/></p>
            <p>The idea is to secure<lb/> agreement&#45;&#45;and to<lb/> avoid discussion&#45;&#45;<lb/> and by agreeing on<lb/> certain essentials be &#91;&#63;&#93;&#44;<lb/> I think this can be<lb/> brought about.  So far<lb/> as Tekhiya &#38; Metim<lb/> and Goel A&#39;Zion are con&#45;<lb/>cerned&#44; I think we could<lb/> get the others to agree<lb/> not to oppose us in the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="5"/>
            <p>3&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>synod&#45;&#45;and then when<lb/> they get home&#44; they could<lb/> do as they pleased&#45;&#45;<lb/> I don&#39;t mean any dis&#45;<lb/>honorable action here&#45;&#45;<lb/> but simply this.  Let<lb/> the synod simply declare<lb/> what is universal&#45;&#45;<lb/> and at the same time<lb/> allow the individual<lb/> members to take liberties.<lb/>  The re&#91;&#63;&#93; would be that<lb/> we would have a Conserva&#45;<lb/>tive ritual firmly established<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="6"/>
            <p>and the Reform&#45;Conser&#45;<lb/>vatives would be just<lb/> where they are now&#45;&#45;<lb/>while we would escape<lb/> dangers.<lb/></p>
            <p>As to myself&#44; I would<lb/> be willing to compromise<lb/> on Mekhayeh Nefashot<lb/> &#38;c&#45;&#45;As it can&#39;t<lb/> alter the facts one way<lb/> or the other&#45;&#45;and is<lb/> of no actual living<lb/> value&#45;&#45;but of course<lb/> I will stand by you in<lb/> anything you may decide.<lb/>  Think over it and act with<lb/> the same wisdom and<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="7"/>
            <p>4<lb/></p>
            <p>forbearance you have<lb/> shown throughout<lb/> this whole seminary<lb/> matter.<lb/></p>
            <p>I will try to see you<lb/> soon.  My wife and<lb/> son are well.<lb/></p>
            <p>Affectionately<lb/>
                J. S. C.<lb/></p>
            <p>I enclose rough<lb/> draft of call for<lb/> Synod<lb/></p>
            </body>
